4️⃣ Gmail Integration
4.1 Authentication

Uses OAuth 2.0 refresh token flow.

Stored in .env:

GMAIL_CLIENT_ID
GMAIL_CLIENT_SECRET
GMAIL_REFRESH_TOKEN
GMAIL_USER

No InstalledAppFlow in production.
No token.json used.

4.2 Polling Strategy

Runs every 30 seconds

Fetches:

q="is:unread"
maxResults=20

Processes only unread emails

Marks email as read ONLY after successful parsing and forwarding

5️⃣ Email Processing Logic
5.1 Ticket Detection

Email considered ticket-related if:

Contains flight-related keywords:

ticket

itinerary

flight

booking

pnr

reservation

OR contains PDF attachment

Future improvements:

Airline sender domain filtering

PNR pattern detection

5.2 Content Extraction Priority

Priority:

PDF attachment text > email body (text/plain > text/html)

If PDF exists:

Extract text in memory

Do NOT save to disk

If no PDF:

Extract plain text

Fallback to HTML text stripping

6️⃣ Ticket Parser Requirements

The LLM parser must extract:

6.1 Booking Details

Booking Date

Phone Number (Passenger)

Booking Reference (PNR)

Class of Travel

Currency

Grand Total

6.2 Passenger Details (Multi Passenger Support)

For each passenger:

Name

Pax Type (ADT / CHD / INF)

Ticket Number

Frequent Flyer Number

Baggage

Meal

Ancillaries

Fare breakdown:

Base Fare

K3 (Airline GST)

Other Taxes

Total (Extracted)

Total (Calculated)

Seats:

Stored per segment

Each seat linked to segment index

6.3 Flight Segments (Multi Segment Support)

Each segment contains:

Flight Number

Booking Class

Departure:

City

Airport Code

Date

Time

Terminal

Arrival:

City

Airport Code

Date

Time

Terminal

Duration (Extracted)

Duration (Calculated)

7️⃣ Calculations

Both Parser and Query System perform calculations.

Parser calculates:

Duration (if missing)

Fare totals

Grand total

Query System recalculates everything for verification.

Parser must:

Never override extracted values

Only compute derived fields

Flag mismatches

8️⃣ Output JSON Schema

High-level structure:

{
  "metadata": {
    "parser_version": "",
    "received_at": "",
    "warnings": [],
    "errors": []
  },
  "booking": {},
  "passengers": [],
  "segments": []
}

Supports:

Multi passenger

Multi segment

Layovers

Round trip

Multicity

9️⃣ Error Handling Rules

If parsing fails:

Do NOT mark email as read

Log error

Retry on next cycle

If forwarding fails:

Do NOT mark as read

If successful:

Mark email as read

Unread = Unprocessed
Read = Successfully Processed

🔟 Non-Responsibilities

Ticket Parser Service will NOT:

Match itinerary

Generate final agency ticket

Perform business decisions

Distribute fares across passengers

Store long-term database state (handled downstream)

